# Feature that speeds up uploads and downloads to s3 buckets.

Use Cases
    - Upload to central bucket from locations spread out
    across the world.
    
    - Transfering TBs of data on regular schedule from
    all around the world.

    - If not able to use all avialble bandwidth to the
    internet.

Requestor Pays

    - Requestor pays can be setup to offload the cost
    of storage and transfer to the AWS IAM user.

    - This is setup on the bucket.

    - Requests that are made must include the
    x-amz-request-payer-header or the RequestPayer
    can be a parameter in the request.

    Hosting static websites in s3
    -Websites can only run client side scripts,
    not server side.
    -Websites that are dynamic that require 
    database connections cannot be hosted in
    s3
    -S3 will scale automatically to accomodate
    demand.